comment.body:
> After disabling OctoPrint, the inotify statistics stay stable at about 20 watches with 2 instances. Before that, I was at >2000 instances.
> 
> > Now I'm just curious what made this issue appear in 2025.05. The octoprint integration hasn't changed much in the last months...
> 
> Maybe it was handled differently in aiohttp or another library that has been bumped?

Octoprint been leaking for a long time. There was a change in aiodns in 2025.5 to be able to detect network configuration changes that needs an inotify handle. While it was leaking before and slowly eating up memory it was a bit more obvious now that we run out of inotify handles as well
